Faiths across Time [4 volumes] - 5,000 Years of Religious History
by J. Gordon Melton
ABC-CLIO | January 2014 | ISBN-10: 1610690257 | True PDF | 2023 pages | 35.4 mb

Covering a vast time span from 3500 BCE to 2009 CE, this set highlights events of all major religions from all corners of the globe. The presentation format is plain, with no graphical representation or time line. Readers will find a succession of chronological entries, including a date, a geographical label (e.g., China, England, Italy), a religious label (e.g., Christianity, Islam, Judaism), and a paragraphÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s worth of highly readable information on the corresponding event. The unique size of this chronology (four volumes) allows for the inclusion of many lesser-known events that would ordinarily be left out of a general-purpose reference work. this work offers so much more than just mindless dates that it can be read in a leisurely manner. And for the sake of those wanting pinpoint access to a particular event, the sets extensive index is included in every volume. This work offers so much more than just mindless dates that it can be read in a leisurely manner. And for the sake of those wanting pinpoint access to a particular event, the sets extensive index is included in every volume.

